com.radiantlogic.iddm.schema

Annotation Type Entity


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Entity
    Marks a class as the Java-based definition of a schema object in IDDM.

    This annotation is used for code-based schema authoring. IDDM will use the annotated class to generate a new schema object. To be successful, the annotated class must:

    • Be a concrete, top-level, public class
    • Have a public, no-arg constructor
    • Contain at least one Attribute annotated field marked as a naming attribute

    For example: 

    {@code

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String name
      Specifies the name to use when generating a schema object from the annotated class.
      String namingKey
      Specifies the attribute name that appears in the LDAP entry's leftmost RDN.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract String name
        Specifies the name to use when generating a schema object from the annotated class.

        If provided, this name will be used when generating a new SchemaObject and is the value returned when calling SchemaObject.getName(). Otherwise, a non-blank default name is automatically generated.

        Default:
        ""

      • namingKey

        public abstract String namingKey
        Specifies the attribute name that appears in the LDAP entry's leftmost RDN.

        If provided, then this value will be used when generating a new SchemaObject and is the value returned when calling SchemaObject.getNamingKey(). Otherwise, a non-blank default naming key is automatically generated.

        Default:
        ""
